  "texts": [
    "This approach allowed for a naturalistic observation of how students integrate LLM-powered educational resources into their learning processes, without imposing additional constraints that could influence their study habits or the study's outcomes.",
    "Student Evaluation.At the end of the semester, students' final grades were used as a primary measure to assess their learning outcomes and the impact of CodeTutor interventions.",
    "While acknowledging that final grades are influenced by various factors, they offer a standardized measure of overall academic success, enabling an assessment of CodeTutor's role in improving student learning outcomes.",
    "Final grades were determined by a weighted average that includes several components for each student: labs (practical miniprojects), assignments (individual coding tasks, such as array summation), mid-terms, and a final exam (comprising questions similar to those in the pre-test).",
    "Note that a student's final grade can surpass 100 if bonus points are awarded throughout the semester."
  ],
